snippet.textDisplay: I don't know who needs to read this, but Cleetus has 1.5M people that like him (and those are only the subscibers). There is no way for him out of all those people to know who is real, who is a poser, who is sane, who is crazy, etc. Frankly, he does not have the time and he has friends already. I'm a nobody with 300 friends on Facebook and it's near impossible to keep up with just that so I can only imagine 1.5 MILLION. One minor accident on the track or at his shop could majorly hurt or ruin him. Something even as minor as a splinter could spell disaster. Even if you wouldn't do that to him, he has no idea and has to assume liability for everyone. Unless he invites you to hang with him, STAY THE HELL AWAY. I think it's safe to say he is far from impressed to see a car guy that likes him and wants to hang with him. We all do.
